main event: A sighting of a fast-moving white object traveling from south to north in Berlin, Germany on 23rd September 1948.
interesting points: The sighting was reported to have occurred at 1630 hours.
The object was described as white and moving rather fast.
There were no photographs or sketches included with the report.
The report is labeled as 'Temporary ATIC Form 329' from 2nd June 1952, indicating it was part of the Air Technical Intelligence Center's records.
The report indicates that the sighting occurred during the post-World War II era in a location of historical significance.
